article.headline: Denver 75, Louisiana-Monroe 65
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- Tyler Bullock scored 22 points to lead Denver to a 75-65 win Saturday over the Louisiana-Monroe Warhawks for the Pioneers' first Sun Belt Conference win this season. It was the first conference loss of the season for Louisiana-Monroe (10-7, 4-1 Sun Belt) and snapped Denver's 11-game losing streak. Denver (2-14, 1-5) never trailed after Adam Tanner made two free throws with five minutes remaining in the first half for a 22-20 lead. Denver led by as much as 21 after DaShawn Walker scored eight unanswered points in the second half to make it 57-36 with 11:08 left. Walker finished with 15 points. Tony Hooper scored 19 points to lead the Warhawks, and Lance Brasher had 18.
